We recommended again that the Municipal Treasurer:

(18) a. submit to the Municipal Accountant the monthly Billing Statements of water consumers;

(19) b. collect on the specified dates all amounts due from water consumers;

(20) c. prepare monthly  a report that summarizes unpaid accounts and the delinquent payees and submit to the Municipal Accountant;

(21) d. prepare   Demand 

Letters monthly to all delinquent water consumers for signature of the Mayor; and,

(22) e. issue Notices of Disconnection to water consumers who fail to adhere with the Demand Letters. 

(23) We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant record in the books the receivables from Waterworks System services based on the billing statements submitted by the Municipal Treasurer and provide for the   necessary allowance for doubtful accounts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive: 

(63) a. Provide the necessary support in enjoining the barangays to establish their own MRFs and to fully implement waste segregation at source;

(64) b. Strictly enforce and intensify the information campaign on the no-littering policy among the residents; and; 

(65) c. Consider embarking on effective projects and programs to support the LGUs ecological solid waste management program.

